%% ScholarForge V1 — Request Lifecycle
%% Source: Derived from Architecture Document §5 + API.md endpoint design
%% Shows the full lifecycle of a "Generate Draft" request from browser to DOCX export

sequenceDiagram
    autonum
    actor User
    participant UI as Next.js Frontend<br/>(Browser)
    participant API as Express Backend<br/>(localhost:3001)
    participant GenWF as GenerationWorkflow
    participant Val as NotesValidator
    participant PB as PromptBuilder
    participant MC as IModelClient
    participant Model as Qwen2.5-3B<br/>(via Ollama/llama.cpp)
    participant OC as OutputCleaner
    participant TE as TemplateEngine
    participant DE as DocxExporter
    participant FS as Local Filesystem

    User->>UI: Enter structured notes,<br/>select template, click "Generate"
    UI->>UI: Validate UI-side (basic checks)
    UI->>API: POST /api/generate/draft<br/>{ notesDocument, voiceProfile, templateSelection }

    API->>GenWF: generateDraft(notes, voice, modelClient)
    GenWF->>Val: validate(notesDocument)

    alt Notes invalid
        Val-->>GenWF: ValidationResult { errors: [...] }
        GenWF-->>API: Error: "Notes validation failed: Section 2 has no bullets"
        API-->>UI: 400 Bad Request<br/>{ error: "NOTES_INVALID", details: [...] }
        UI-->>User: Display specific validation errors inline
    end

    Val-->>GenWF: ValidationResult { valid: true }

    loop For each NoteSection (section-by-section generation)
        GenWF->>PB: build(section, voiceProfile, sectionTemplate)
        PB-->>GenWF: Prompt string (context-budget-respecting)
        GenWF->>MC: generate(prompt, options)
        MC->>Model: localhost HTTP / IPC call<br/>(timeout: configured ms)

        alt Model call succeeds
            Model-->>MC: Raw text response
            MC-->>GenWF: rawText
        else Model fails (OOM, timeout, not running)
            MC-->>GenWF: throws ModelClientError
            GenWF->>GenWF: Log failure, flag section,<br/>continue to next section<br/>(partial-failure tolerance)
        end

        GenWF->>OC: clean(rawText)
        OC-->>GenWF: cleanedText + isAcceptable flag

        alt Output unacceptable (empty/degenerate)
            GenWF->>PB: rebuild with "write at least N sentences" instruction
            PB-->>GenWF: adjusted prompt
            GenWF->>MC: generate(adjustedPrompt)
            MC-->>GenWF: retryRawText
            GenWF->>OC: clean(retryRawText)
            OC-->>GenWF: cleanedText
        end

        GenWF->>GenWF: Assemble DraftSection<br/>{ id, sourceSectionId, heading, content }
    end

    GenWF-->>API: Draft { sections: DraftSection[] }<br/>(possibly with failedSectionIds[])

    API-->>UI: 200 OK<br/>{ draft, failedSections }

    opt User clicks "Apply IEEE Formatting"
        UI->>API: POST /api/format/apply<br/>{ draft, templateSelection: "ieee_us_letter" }
        API->>TE: apply(draft, selection)
        TE-->>API: FormattedDocument { sections, styleSheet, references }
        API-->>UI: 200 OK { formattedDocument }
    end

    opt User clicks "Export DOCX"
        UI->>API: POST /api/export/docx<br/>{ formattedDocument, outputPath }
        API->>DE: export(formattedDocument, path)
        DE->>FS: Write .docx (via DocxRenderer + StyleMapper)
        FS-->>DE: file path
        DE-->>API: ExportResult { path, sizeBytes }
        API-->>UI: 200 OK { filePath, sizeBytes }
        UI-->>User: "Export complete — file saved to {path}"
    end

    Note over UI,FS: Throughout: AutosaveScheduler fires on every<br/>state-changing event, atomically writing<br/>the full SessionState to a .scholarforge file.
